x4freetext: The target of approximately 10 mg/cm**2 of isotopically
enriched Pd-104 (80%) and Pd-102 (78%) were prepared
by deposition on thin polyethylene backings.
The gamma-ray singles spectra measurements were
performed with a 40cm3 Ge(Li) detector at 45 degree to
the beam direction. The energy resolution of this
calibrated spectrometer was 2.2 keV (FWHM) for the
*EN-RSL-FW*. Overall energy resolution
the Grenoble variable-energy cyclotron.
